`se` ships in two flavors. The Plane-sync wiring differs slightly between
them — pick the row that matches how you installed `se`:

| Install mode | How you got it | Hook wiring |
|--------------|----------------|-------------|
| **Binary** | `curl -sL .../install.sh \\| bash` → `se` on PATH | Run `se repos add --plane-project-id <UUID>`. The auto-generated `<target-repo>/.grava/hooks/plane-sync.sh` shim calls `se plane-sync` — the bundled binary locates its own data, no `STELLAR_ENGINE_HOME` needed. |
